Olam International Ltd. (OLAM) , a
Singapore-based farm commodities trader, will invest 413 billion
 CFA francs  ($890 million) in a  palm oil  project in Gabon, the
African nationâ€™s Ministry of Agriculture said.  The company plans to produce 280,000 metric tons of palm
oil in the first phase of the project, the Libreville-based
ministry said in an e-mailed statement yesterday. The first
phase will start in October with a second phase in 2013, it
